#!/bin/bash
set -e

# Challenge 4 Setup: State Management & CLI
echo "Setting up Challenge 4: State Management & CLI..."

# Clean workspace
cd /root/terraform-lab
terraform destroy -auto-approve 2>/dev/null || true
rm -rf *
rm -rf .terraform*
rm -rf terraform.tfstate*

# Create example solution from GitHub repo
mkdir -p /root/terraform-lab-solutions/challenge-04
cp -r /root/lab-assets/tf-100-fundamentals-lab/assets/challenge-04/* /root/terraform-lab-solutions/challenge-04/

# Return to workspace
cd /root/terraform-lab

# Display welcome message
cat << 'EOF'

╔════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║                                                                ║
║            Challenge 4: State Management & CLI                 ║
║                                                                ║
╚════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

In this challenge, you'll master Terraform's state system and CLI:

  • Understanding and inspecting state
  • State modification commands
  • Workspaces for environment management
  • Terraform console for interactive exploration
  • Debugging with logging
  • Import and state operations

📁 Working Directory: /root/terraform-lab
📚 Example Solution: /root/terraform-lab-solutions/challenge-04

Key Skills:
  • terraform state list/show/mv/rm
  • terraform workspace new/select/list
  • terraform console
  • terraform import
  • TF_LOG environment variables

Follow the instructions in the assignment to complete the challenge!

EOF

echo "Challenge 4 setup complete!"

